               <msContents>
                  <summary>In Minasian collection, there are 19 manuscripts under the generic title of Adʿīyah [Prayers]. The reason is that their individual titles have remained unknown for different reasons, including defective incipits and explicits.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="WadhMinasian_735-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Persian</textLang>
                     <note type="content-genre">Prayers</note>
                     <author>
                        
                        
                        <persName xml:lang="en">Anonymous</persName>
                        
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">[Adʿīyah]</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa">[ادعیه]</title>
                     <note xml:lang="en">A collection of prayers, including for amulets and phylacteries (scattered pieces, also survived from various books, but mostly prayer books).</note>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسمله، مقال دوم در اعمال لیالی و ایام هفته و آن چهارده بابست مشتمل بر اعمال … هنگام هفته که هفت شب و هفت روز است…</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa" defective="true">… یا رب موضع کل شکوی و شاهد کل نجوی و حاضر کل ملاء و منتهی کل حاجة و فرح کل…</explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="en">None.</colophon>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>FAW 49</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
